                                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
                                <polyline points="14 7 19 12 14 17" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="font-display text-3xl tracking-tight mb-3">Primary Path First</h3>
                        <p class="text-sf-red font-mono text-sm mb-4">Are we designing for the 95% case or getting distracted by edge cases?</p>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
                            Make the 80% path boring, resilient, and fast to understand. Keep the primary path simple. Contain edge cases behind seams. When the primary path is boring, everything else becomes easier. Testing becomes straightforward. Debugging becomes faster. Onboarding becomes smoother. Edge cases are real &mdash; the question is not whether to handle them, but where.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

