                                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">Elena's payment system could handle anything &mdash; currency conversion for 147 countries, fraud detection for patterns nobody had observed, retry logic for seventeen failure scenarios. There was just one problem: processing a simple domestic credit card payment took four thousand lines of code to trace. The primary path had become invisible, buried under layers of edge-case handling.</p>
